The Nigeria Governors’ Forum (NGF)  meeting  was unable to hold last night for lack of quorum. Of the 36 states of the federation, only Zamfara, Jigawa, Niger, Adamawa, Bauchi  Kaduna, Enugu, Katsina, Nasarawa states were represented. The governors were expected to deliberate on the new National Minimum Wage before today’s meeting of the National Economic Council (NEC). Recall that the federal government had said it would make its final decision on the minimum wage after the NEC meeting today. Also yesterday, the director-general of the President Muhammadu Campaign Organisation, Rotimi Amaechi met with governors of the All Progressive Congress (APC) at the NGF secretariat.